<body>

<h1>{$node_name}</h1>

<p>The option "Backup/Restore" of the menu "System" allows you to back up and restore the configuration of Issabel. If you have made a backup any time before this will appear in the list <i>(Figure 1)</i>. To download a backup from the list, just click on the name of the tar file. </p>
<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_backup_restore.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 1</p></div>
<br />

<h2>Perform a Backup</h2>

<p>To create a backup just click on "Perform a Backup" button. Select all the configurations you want to back up from Issabel and click on "Process" button.</p>
<br />
<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_backup.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 2</p></div>
<br />

<h2>Restore a Backup</h2>

<p>In the list of backups <i>(Figure 1)</i> click on "Restore" button locate on the right of the backup you want to restore. Then select the configuration to restore and click on "Process" button <i>(Figure 3)</i>.</p>

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_restore.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 3</p></div>
<br />

<h2>FTP Backup</h2>

<p>To use a FTP Server to upload and download backups just click on "FTP Backup" button <i>(Figure 1)</i>. First, fill out the required information to connect with your FTP Server and then click on "Save" button to save changes.</p>
<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_FTP1.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 4</p></div>
<br />
<h3>Uploading files to FTP server</h3>
<p>To upload backups to the FTP server you must drag the backup file from Local section to Server FTP section.</p>

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_FTP2.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 5</p></div>
<br />

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_FTP3.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 6</p></div>
<br />

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_FTP4.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 7</p></div>
<br />
<h3>Downloading files from FTP server</h3>
<p>To download backup files to Issabel Server just drag the file from Server FTP section to Local section.</p>

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_FTP5.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 8</p></div>
<br />

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_FTP6.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 9</p></div>
<br />

<div class="hlp_figures"><img src="../modules/{$node_id}/images/hlp_FTP7.png" border="0" />
<p>Figure 10</p></div>
<br />
</body>
